    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "The fallacy of Hyperbolic Discounting occurs when someone too heavily weighs the importance of a present reward over a significantly greater reward in the near future, but only slightly differs in their valuations of those two rewards if they are to be received in the far future. The personâ€™s preferences are biased toward the present.",
